320096 SpringUnknow Advanced Routing Principles 32524 LANS and Routing AND32521 WANS and VLANS The lower case 'c' after the subject code indicates that the subject is a corequisite. See 32521 WANs and VLANs.
It extends skills and knowledge in route optimisation and redistribution, router and routing protocol hardening, scalable interior and exterior routing protocols (OSPF, EIGRP, BGP) and NAT. The subject is run in the UTS Cisco Systems Network Academy. Cisco routers are programmed as part of practical work. The subject is part of a sequence which will allow students to prepare for the CCNP industry certification.
